--------------------------------

Save this as docker-compose.yml in your project folder.

Start both containers:

docker-compose up -d


Verify:

docker ps


MongoDB → port 27017

Mongo Express → port 8081

Access Mongo Express in browser:

http://localhost:8081


This setup ensures:

Containers are on the same network (jai-work)

Data is persisted in mongo-data volume

Mongo Express connects automatically to MongoDB using container name

Both containers restart automatically if stopped





docker run -d --name mongo-exp --network jai-work -e MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_USERNAME=admin -e MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_PASSWORD=password -e ME_CONFIG_MONGODB_ADMINUSERNAME=admin -e ME_CONFIG_MONGODB_ADMINPASSWORD=password -e ME_CONFIG_MONGODB_SERVER=mongodb -p 8081:8081 mongo-express



docker run -d --name mongodb --network jai-work -e MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_USERNAME=admin -e MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_PASSWORD=password -p 27017:27017 -v my-data:/data/db mongo:latest docker run -d --name mongodb --network jai-work -e MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_USERNAME=admin -e MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_PASSWORD=password -p 27017:27017 -v my-data:/data/db mongo:latest

